7 Subchapter 4. Farm Security Special Fund
8 § 4631. DEFINITIONS
9 As used in this subchapter:
10 (1) “Eligible weather condition” means any of the following weather
11 conditions that are found to be closely correlated with agricultural income
12 losses:
13 (A) high winds;
14 (B) excessive moisture, intense precipitation, or flooding;
15 (C) extreme heat;
16 (D) abnormal freeze conditions;
17 (E) widespread fire event;
18 (F) hail;
19 (G) drought; or
20 (H) any other severe weather or growing conditions impacting
21 agricultural income, as determined by the Review Board.
