8 § 4632. FARM SECURITY SPECIAL FUND
9 (a) There is established the Farm Security Special Fund to be administered
10 by the Secretary of Agriculture, Food and Markets and that shall be managed
11 in accordance with 32 V.S.A. chapter 7, subchapter 5. The Fund shall consist
12 of:
13 (1) funds transferred by the General Assembly;
14 (2) funds from public and private sources that the Secretary accepts for
15 the Fund; and
16 (3) funds from federal government aid for State support of farmers
17 suffering income loss due to weather conditions.
18 (b) The Secretary of Agriculture, Food and Markets shall ensure language
19 accessibility of the Fund through procurement and provision of interpretation
20 and translation services.
