3 § 4633. FARM SECURITY SPECIAL FUND; GRANTS
4 (a) The Secretary, after consultation with the Review Board, shall award
5 grants from the Farm Security Special Fund to farms that have incurred
6 financial losses or expenses due to an eligible weather condition.
7 (1) Grants from the fund shall be in an amount that reimburses a farm
8 for up to 50 percent of uninsured or otherwise uncovered losses due to eligible
9 weather conditions, up to a maximum award of $150,000.00 total per year per
10 qualified applicant farm.
11 (2) The Secretary shall establish criteria for the amount of an award
12 based on the annual net income of the farm in relation to the median net
13 income of all farms in Vermont.
14 (3) The Secretary may verify the occurrence of an eligible weather
15 condition claimed under this section through a site visit or through use of
16 available data from the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration,
17 from other federal or State certified weather data sources, or from other public
18 or private weather or satellite data or models.
19 (4) Losses reimbursable by a grant under this section include:
20 (A) wages or compensation;
