9 § 4634. FARM SECURITY SPECIAL FUND REVIEW BOARD
10 (a) Creation. There is created the Farm Security Special Fund Review
11 Board, which for administrative purposes shall be attached to the Agency of
12 Agriculture, Food and Markets.
13 (b) Organization of Board. The Board shall be composed of:
14 (1) the Secretary of Agriculture, Food and Markets or designee, who
15 shall serve as chair;
16 (2) the State Chief Recovery Officer or designee;
17 (3) representatives of three agricultural organizations who can
18 demonstrate expertise in dealing with all sizes and types of farms in Vermont,
19 whether through granting funds, offering technical assistance or advocacy and
20 have a proven track record of working with farmers, appointed by the
21 Secretary of Agriculture, Food and Markets; and
